<TITLE> Police arrest OMS dealer for 'hiding' rice </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 7 (bdnews24.com)An OMS dealer was arrested in Mirpur Monday on charges of hiding instead of selling 13 sacks of rice, a police officer said. The arrested dealer is Jamal Hossain, proprietor of Milon Traders at Bara Bagbazar in Mirpur. Sub-inspector Kuddus Fakir of Mirpur Police Station told bdnews24.com that a case had been filed against Jamal for hiding rice meant for open market sale. The arrest came after the food directorate had alerted the police to the matter, sub-inspector of food Iskandar Ali told bdnews24.com. bdnews
